{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it illegal for discrimination of those with non-offensive visible tattoos.",
        "additional_details": "Article 1 of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights: \u201cAll human beings are born free and equal in dignity and rights\".\r\n\r\nArticle 10 of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights: \"The right to communicate and express yourself in any medium, including words, pictures and actions\".\r\n\r\nTwo of our Basic human rights that employers violate. Discrimination against Race, Gender, Age, Sexual Orientation & Disabilities have all been addressed, now we should address the discrimination of visible body art.",
        "background": "Times are changing, and we as a country have to change with them.  Many workplaces can and will choose to discriminate against those who have visible tattoos.  Non-discrimination is a cross-cutting principle in international human rights law.",
